BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:ibPzAES2Bt3aTA9c6moC0
SUMMARY:IMPROV 100 TUESDAYS - Intro to Improv: Say Yes!\\\, SPRING'26
DTSTAMP:20260314T160738Z
DTSTART:20260324T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Say yes! Learn to listen\\\, connect\\\, play and use your own 
	life to create stories with others! An 8 week intro to improvised theatre!
	\\n\\n\\n\\nDiscover Unexpected Productions’ philosophy of improvisation\\
	\, developed over our 43 years of improvising in Seattle! \\nYou’ll learn 
	how to actively listen\\\, to use your own life to create collaborative st
	ories\\\, and you’ll work on the fundamental principles of improvisation: 
	what it means to say\\\, “Yes\\\, And”\\\, how to tell stories that includ
	e everyone in the room\\\, how to stop worrying about failing\\\, and the 
	games and concepts behind what we do on stages around the world! \\nUnder 
	the guidance of one of our best Seattle improv teachers\\\, you will learn
	 to:· \\n\\nBe a Better Listener\\nConquer Fears\\nSpark Creativity\\nMeet
	 New People & Make New Friends\\nBecome a Better Problem Solver\\nGain Con
	fidence·\\nFail With Grace (and Maybe Even Enjoy It)\\nSay Yes More in You
	r Life\\nGet Out of Your Comfort Zone\\nBecome a Better Public Speaker\\nD
	iscover More About Yourself\\n…and have a blast doing it!\\n\\nTime and Da
	tes: Tuesdays for eight (8) weeks\\\, from March 24 to May 22\\\, 7pm to 9
	:30pm \\nNOTE: Attendance at the first session of your course is mandatory
	 as it sets the agenda for the entire quarter. If you think you will have 
	to miss the first class\\\, please consider registering for the next quart
	er. \\nNo Prerequisites. All students begin at this level\\\, even those w
	ith existing improv experience. It’s a prerequisite to the other levels. \
	\nLocation: 5700 6th Ave St\\\, Suite 109\\\, Umbrella Room\\\, Seattle\\\
	, WA 98108 (In Georgetown\\\, south of downtown\\\, with plenty of parking
	.) \\nMaximum Students: 16 \\nCost: Ticket price $295.00 \\nAge: 18 and ab
	ove \\n**Cancellation policy: If you must cancel before the first class\\\
	, we can only offer credit towards the same level class next quarter. We a
	re unable to offer refunds. If you cancel after the first class we cannot 
	offer credit towards a future class. Again\\\, we are unable to offer refu
	nds.\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/improv-100-tuesdays-in
	tro-to-improv-build-confidence-spring-26/\n\nFrom Unexpected Productions
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/improv-100-tuesdays-intro-t
	o-improv-build-confidence-spring-26/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions Improv School ISSAQUAH/EASTSIDE\\\, 1315 NW
	 Mall Street\\\, Suite 4\\\, Issaquah\\\, WA\\\, 98108\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:unexpected-productions
CATEGORIES:Unexpected Productions
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
